# Vanilla Forums Repository Guide

## When to use
- Navigating the vanillaforums GitHub org repos
- Understanding Vanilla's platform architecture
- Looking up how a specific Vanilla subsystem works
- Finding reference code for building custom themes or plugins

## Repository Map

| Repo | Use for | Branch |
|------|---------|--------|
| `vanillaforums/spotify` | Production Spotify theme work | `master` (prod), `stage`, `develop` |
| `vanillaforums/Spotify-trial` | Spotify-specific widget examples (Stars programme, personalised feed) | `master`, `feature/adam-demo` |
| `vanillaforums/vanilla-local` | Platform architecture reference, understanding how Vanilla works | `release/2026.002` |
| `vanillaforums/community` | Irrelevant (Vanilla's own support site theme) | `master` |

## Accessing Repo Content

```bash
# List repos
gh api orgs/vanillaforums/repos --jq '.[].name'

# Get file tree
gh api repos/vanillaforums/<repo>/git/trees/<branch>?recursive=1 --jq '.tree[].path'

# Read a file (base64-decode)
gh api repos/vanillaforums/<repo>/contents/<path> --jq '.content' | base64 -d

# Recent commits
gh api repos/vanillaforums/<repo>/commits?per_page=20

# Branches
gh api repos/vanillaforums/<repo>/branches

# PRs
gh api repos/vanillaforums/<repo>/pulls?state=all
```

## vanilla-local Architecture (The Platform)

This is the reference for understanding how Vanilla works. Key directories:

```
vanilla-local/
├── applications/
│   ├── dashboard/      # Admin backend (settings, users, roles, permissions)
│   ├── vanilla/        # Core forum (discussions, categories, comments)
│   ├── conversations/  # Private messaging
│   └── groups/         # Sub-communities / groups
├── library/
│   ├── Garden/         # Core framework (HTTP, events, DI, exceptions)
│   └── Vanilla/
│       ├── Layout/     # Layout Editor + Hydrator (widget rendering system)
│       ├── Theme/      # ThemeService, theme providers, variable resolution
│       ├── Models/     # Base model classes
│       └── Widgets/    # Widget base classes and interfaces
├── plugins/            # 37 bundled plugins (see below)
├── addons/themes/      # Reference themes
│   ├── theme-foundation/   # Modern asset-based theme (THE template to follow)
│   ├── theme-boilerplate/  # Legacy SCSS starter
│   ├── lavendermoon/       # Dark theme example
│   └── lavendersun/        # Light theme example
├── build/              # Vite/webpack config, Storybook
├── cli/                # `vnla` CLI tool
├── docker/             # Dev environment containers
├── docs/               # Backend + frontend architecture docs
├── packages/           # Internal npm packages (vanilla-ui, vanilla-i18n)
└── tests/              # PHPUnit + Vitest
```

## Key Subsystems

### Layout Editor + Hydrator
- `library/Vanilla/Layout/LayoutHydrator.php` — server-side widget resolution
- `GET /api/v2/layouts/lookup-hydrate` — hydrates layout specs into React trees
- Admins drag widgets onto pages in the Layout Editor
- Widgets register via `addReactResolver` in container rules

### Theme System
- `library/Vanilla/Theme/ThemeService.php` — manages theme providers
- Supports theme inheritance (max 3 levels)
- Mobile vs desktop theme separation
- `DataDrivenTheme` feature flag enables modern React header

### Addon System
- Everything is an addon: applications, plugins, themes
- `addon.json` manifest required for each
- Enabled via `$Configuration['EnabledPlugins']` or `$Configuration['EnabledApplications']`

### Event System
- Convention-based: `controllerName_eventName_handler`
- `base_render_before` fires on every page
- Models emit `afterSave`, `beforeDelete`, etc.

